title: Cardinals tight end Darren Fells out 2-3 weeks with shoulder sprain
text: Cardinals tight end Darren Fells out 2-3 weeks with shoulder sprain Quote: According to Kent Somers of the Arizona Republic , Cardinals tight end Darren Fells will be out two to three weeks with a shoulder sprain suffered in yesterdayÂ’s loss at Pittsburgh. Fells had a strong opener as a receiver against the Saints, though he was previously considered more of a blocker. Veteran Jermaine Gresham will have to play a bigger role now. Opportunity for Niklas to see some playing time?
